article.headline: Toledo beats Ball State 45-13 in game with 10 turnovers
article.description: Bryant Koback had two first-half touchdown runs and Toledo beat Ball State 45-13 on Wednesday night in a game that saw each team commit five turnovers.
article.linkText: Toledo beats Ball State 45-13 in game with 10 turnovers

images.name: Thompson scores 23-yard TD
images.caption: Cody Thompson makes a shoe-string catch and then runs in a 23-yard touchdown to give Toledo a 31-13.

video.headline: Thompson scores 23-yard TD
video.caption: Cody Thompson makes a shoe-string catch and then runs in a 23-yard touchdown to give Toledo a 31-13.
video.title: Thompson scores 23-yard TD
video.description: Cody Thompson makes a shoe-string catch and then runs in a 23-yard touchdown to give Toledo a 31-13.

article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio -- Bryant Koback had two first-half touchdown runs and Toledo beat Ball State 45-13 on Wednesday night in a game that saw each team commit five turnovers. The Rockets (5-4, 3-2 Mid-American) scored 21 points in less than 2 1/2 minutes in the first quarter. Koback opened the scoring with a 19-yard run, seven plays after Willie Ross recovered a fumble. Ball State (3-7, 2-4) then went three-and-out and the Rockets drove 77 yards in just 45 seconds with the help of a 51-yard pass play. Art Thompkins capped the drive with a 1-yard run. Three plays after the ensuing kickoff, Drew Plitt was strip-sacked by Terrance Taylor with Tuzar Skipper racing to the end zone to dive on the ball for a 21-0 lead. Plitt threw an 18-yard touchdown pass to Riley Miller, who had 101 yards receiving, early in the second quarter but soon the Rockets made it 28-7 on Koback's 3-yard run that came 10 plays after Zachary Ford intercepted Plitt. Jameson Vest added his school-record 69th career field goal for a 31-7 lead late in the third quarter. Peters, starting in place of injured Mitchell Guadagni, threw for 327 yards and two touchdowns but tossed four of Toledo's five interceptions. Diontae Johnson had 100 yards receiving for Toledo. The teams combined for 968 yards offense.

videos.headline: Koback runs in a 19-yard TD
videos.description: Bryant Koback takes the handoff and makes defenders miss to score a 19-yard touchdown to give Toledo a 7-0 lead.

videos.headline: Johnson erupts for 57-yard gain
videos.description: Eli Peters passes to Diontae Johnson who weaves in and out of traffic for a 57-yard gain that puts Toledo in the red zone.

videos.headline: Toledo defense strips, scoops and scores
videos.description: Drew Plitt gets stripped sack by Toledo's Terrance Taylor and the ball is recovered in the end zone by Tuzar Skipper for a touchdown.

videos.headline: Plitt connects with Miller for 18-yard TD
videos.description: QB Drew Plitt moves out the pocket and delivers an 18-yard touchdown pass to Riley Miller to put Ball State on the board.

videos.headline: Ball State's Miller hauls in interception
videos.description: Toledo QB Eli Peters throws it deep in the hopes of getting a four-touchdown lead, but is picked off by Ball State's Josh Miller.

videos.headline: Crazy catch called back for penalty
videos.description: Ball State's Justin Hall who makes a beautiful catch, then fights and extends for a touchdown, but it is call back on a offensive pass interference call.

videos.headline: Plitt finds Miller for a 47-yard gain
videos.description: Off a flea flicker, Drew Plitt connects with Riley Miller for a 47-yard gain to end the 3rd quarter down 24 versus Toledo.

videos.headline: Uzodinma brings in a one-handed interception
videos.description: Ball State's Amechi Uzodinma pulls off his best Odell Beckham Jr. impersonation with a one-handed interception.
